# Database

## Schema (see `supabase/migrations/`)

Core tables: `profiles`, `organizations`, `organization_members`, `projects`, `project_updates`, `decks`, `slides`, `slide_assets`, `brand_kits`, `exports`, `ai_generations`.

## RLS

- All public tables have RLS enabled
- Access gated by `is_org_member(org_id)` helper (security definer)
- Never disable RLS or use service role in user-facing code paths

## Migrations

- One migration per logical change; numbered `00N_description.sql`
- Include RLS policies in the same migration as table creation
- Test policies: member can CRUD own org data; non-member gets zero rows

## JSONB columns

- `project_updates.*` — structured update fields (goals, metrics, risks, etc.)
- `slides.content` — matches `SlideContent` type
- `decks.outline` — matches `DeckOutline` type

## Storage buckets

Path pattern: `{org_id}/{entity_id}/{filename}`

Buckets: `screenshots`, `brand-logos`, `slide-assets`, `exports` (all private).

## Rules

- Index foreign keys (`deck_id`, `org_id`, `project_id`)
- Use `timestamptz` for all timestamps
- `ON DELETE CASCADE` for child rows; `SET NULL` only where intentional
